🧠 Task 1 – AI Prompting in 2026
📌 Objective
The objective of this lab was to understand modern AI prompting techniques and how different prompt structures affect AI-generated outputs.

📚 Summary of Learning
This lab demonstrated that prompting is not just asking questions, but designing structured instructions for AI systems.
Key concepts learned:
Clear instructions improve output quality
Context improves relevance
Role-based prompting enhances specialization
Structured outputs improve usability
Iterative refinement improves results

⚠️ Challenges Faced
Receiving generic responses from vague prompts
Inconsistent formatting in outputs
Overly long or irrelevant responses
Difficulty in refining prompts initially

💡 Key Takeaway
Better prompts lead to better AI results. Prompt engineering is an essential skill for working effectively with AI systems.

