📊 Task 3 – Lecture Slide Generation Using LLMs
📌 Objective
To use a Large Language Model (NotebookLM) to analyze a lecture and generate presentation slides automatically.

🧠 Tools Used
NotebookLM (Google)
AI-101 Orientation Lecture (YouTube)
Slide Deck Generation Feature

⚙️ Process Followed
Step 1 – Lecture Input
The AI-101 orientation lecture was added into NotebookLM.
Step 2 – Content Analysis
NotebookLM analyzed the lecture transcript and extracted key concepts.
Step 3 – Slide Generation
The built-in Slide Deck feature automatically generated a structured presentation.
Step 4 – Review Process
Slides were reviewed to ensure:
Correct coverage of topics
Logical structure
Relevance to lecture content

❌ Prompts Used
No custom prompts were used.
NotebookLM’s automatic Slide Deck feature handled the entire generation process.

⚠️ Challenges Faced
Ensuring correct lecture import
Verifying accuracy of generated slides
Organizing final output for submission

💡 Key Learnings
LLMs can automatically convert lectures into presentations
AI reduces manual effort in documentation
Human review is still important for accuracy
NotebookLM is effective for academic content transformation

🎯 Final Outcome
Successfully generated lecture slides using LLM
No manual prompting required
Learned AI-based content transformation workflow

